# Agent Keep — scoped deploy privilege (install at /etc/sudoers.d/agent-keep, mode 0440).
# Allows ONLY the fixed root deploy helper; validated with `visudo -c` at install.
# Re-namespaced from the Foundry's sudoers-agent-foundry (ADR 0001 transplant).
#
# This permits the ONE binary with no argument restriction, so the helper ITSELF
# is the trust boundary. The helper validates every <slug> against a strict
# [a-z0-9-] pattern before it reaches a path or unit name (see
# deploy/agent-keep-deploy), so its subcommands taking a <slug> do NOT widen this
# privilege. Replace <deploy-user> with the login that runs deploy.sh on this
# host (per .verity/deploy-access.md, the NSAF dev server login is `smahoney`),
# then install as /etc/sudoers.d/agent-keep (mode 0440) and check with `visudo -c`.
<deploy-user> ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/local/sbin/agent-keep-deploy
